Secure with binder clips and check length before adding glue. Remove binder clip and apply glue to the inside of the folded area. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/ef\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/ef\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":312,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":514.6703296703297,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Replace binder clip and allow clip to remain on the strap for a little more than an hour. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d6\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d6\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Repeat step on the other side of the leather strap. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d1\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d1\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

text:
 Gather all the things you need.  Attach the swivel hooks to the d-rings. You can slide the hooks through the small slit in the rings. Size your leather strap. Decide how long you want the strap to be and then cut to the appropriate length. Allow for at least 2 additional inches on each side as you will be folding the ends to secure hooks in place. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/cd\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/cd\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Lay d-rings on each side of the camera strap and fold over. Secure with binder clips and check length before adding glue. Remove binder clip and apply glue to the inside of the folded area. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/ef\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/ef\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":312,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":514.6703296703297,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Replace binder clip and allow clip to remain on the strap for a little more than an hour. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d6\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d6\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Repeat step on the other side of the leather strap. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d1\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d1\/Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Leather-Camera-Strap-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Attach the smaller rings to each side of your camera. You may already have a set of rings from a previous camera strap, however, if you chose a different color you may want to purchase new ones. Remove binder clips from strap when completely dry and use!  Finished
